## CRITICAL: Fill in a Table Activity Structure (activity_fill_in_a_table)

**Form-based input fields:**
- Use grid layouts: `grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4` for responsive form rows
- Input containers: `p-4 rounded bg-gray-100 flex items-center` with relative positioning
- Labels: Use `font-bold whitespace-nowrap` with proper `data-id` attributes
- **CRITICAL**: ALL input fields MUST have `data-activity-item="item-N"` attribute (item-1, item-2, item-3, etc.)
- Inputs: `border border-gray-300 rounded p-2 w-full` or sized appropriately
- Multiple inputs per row: Use flex layouts with proper spacing

**Title and instruction pattern:**
- Title with background: `text-2xl font-bold mb-4 bg-green-200 -mr-4 p-4 pr-8 rounded-lg`
- Instruction with icon: `<i class="fas fa-pen-to-square text-blue-700 mr-2"></i>` + instruction text

Example fill in table activity:
```html
<section data-section-type="activity_fill_in_a_table" role="activity" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
  <div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 bg-green-200 -mr-4 p-4 pr-8 rounded-lg" data-id="text-10-0">
      Form title here
    </h1>
    <img class="rounded-full" src="images/image.png" alt="" data-id="img-10-0">
  </div>

  <p class="text-lg mb-6 text-center">
    <i class="fas fa-pen-to-square text-blue-700 mr-2"></i>
    <span data-id="text-10-1">Instructions here</span>
  </p>

  <div class="activity-text">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
      <div class="p-4 rounded bg-gray-100 flex items-center">
        <label for="field1" class="mr-2 font-bold whitespace-nowrap" data-id="text-10-3">
          Label text
        </label>
        <input type="text" id="field1" data-activity-item="item-1" class="border border-gray-300 rounded p-2 w-full">
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 mb-6">
      <div class="p-4 rounded bg-gray-100 flex items-center">
        <label for="field2" class="mr-2 font-bold" data-id="text-10-6">First part</label>
        <input type="text" id="field2" data-activity-item="item-2" class="border border-gray-300 rounded p-2 w-24 sm:w-32">
        <label for="field3" class="mx-2 font-bold whitespace-nowrap" data-id="text-10-7">Second part</label>
        <input type="text" id="field3" data-activity-item="item-3" class="border border-gray-300 rounded p-2 w-24 sm:w-32">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
```

**Key requirements:**
- Use `activity-text` class to wrap all form content
- Each input group gets `bg-gray-100` background with padding
- Labels must have `data-id` attributes matching provided text IDs
- Use appropriate input widths (`w-full`, `w-24`, `sm:w-32`) based on expected content length
- Maintain consistent spacing with `mb-6` between sections
- Title typically has `bg-green-200` background with special styling
- VALIDATION: After generating HTML, verify that every `<input>` element has `data-activity-item="item-X"`. If any input is missing it, FIX IT before responding.

### CRITICAL RULE: The <section> tag MUST NOT contain raw text nodes.
- Every textual snippet MUST be inside an element (h1, p, span, label, th, td, etc.) WITH a valid data-id attribute.
- Do NOT place literal text directly between <section> and its first child element.
- If grouping text like "Title and Image" is needed, either omit it or place it in a <p> with a provided data-id.
- Do not duplicate data-id values; each data-id must be unique within the document.
